This magnificent insect I have named in honour of the president 0f the Linnean Society. It is almost impossible to convey by description an idea of the beauty of this species. Its external appearance is of a. light beryl colour: when examined under the lens, it has the appearance of mother-of-pearl, and closely resembles the feathery scales of the Lepidoptera.

The nature and causes of the colouring matter of insects is very imperfectly understood.
